11/11/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Floods hit northern Albania on Wednesday (November 10th), forcing authorities to evacuate a village and call for further precaution measures. The national road linking the city and the border with Montenegro was cut on Wednesday, while 40 houses are under water. Heavy rains have been pouring over the region for two days. The Shkodra region has been hit by floods several times in the past year. (Balkan Web, Top News, News 24 - 10/11/10)
